Section 10: Securing Microservices with Spring Security
 Lecture 10.1 Understand security

* Spring Security
  * Spring Security is a modern framework for a modern age
  * Centered around AuthenticationProviders (and specialized UserDetailService)
  * Provides modeules for all sorts of identity provider systems
    (Active Directory, LDAP, PAM, Kerberos, OAuth, etc)

* Security Techniques
  * HTTP Basic - Usernames and Passwords
  * X509 SSL Certificates - Mutual authentication
  * OAuth - A way for users to authorize applications to access their
    information without giving them passwords

